25|$|In 2006, {{a budget}} {{deadlock}} between the Republican-controlled House of Delegates and the Republican-controlled Senate {{resulted in the}} legislative session extending far beyond its normal term {{as well as a}} special session. In general, the Democrats favored a progressive income tax and sought to eliminate the <b>sales</b> <b>tax</b> <b>on</b> groceries.|$|E
