500|$|During his 2008 candidacy, Gravel {{favored a}} {{progressive}} FairTax scheme, which would abolish the Internal Revenue Service, eliminate the {{federal income tax}} (which Gravel referred to as [...] "corrupt"), and impose a national <b>sales</b> <b>tax.</b> To offset the new <b>sales</b> <b>taxes</b> <b>on</b> essential goods, Gravel's plan called for monthly government rebate payments to individuals and families.|$|R
